{"TopicId":119143,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"77 Industries: Heavy Trucking Division.","CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T11:07:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-08-23T11:07:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E77 industries Presents:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E77I - LRHF \u0022Long Range Heavy Friend\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/HurdP/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nMy first truck with trailer. Stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nFeatures:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nModern truck with retro front styling.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nCabin on flexible mount for more driver comfort.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nPassive safety features.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nAbility to drive with one or more wheels broken.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nSpecial suspension with bump stop/shock absorbers.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nConvert-O-Tron 125 and fuel cell arrays.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nBunk with colour TV.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nTractor unit: 16.7 tons with fuel tanks full.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nThis combination: guess ;-)\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nMax cornering speed with full wheel deflection: 11 m/s on level terrain, depends on mass.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nMax speed on level terrain: 24.7 m/s.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nMax allowed speed: 29 m/s.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nTractor unit: 160 parts.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nTotal part count: 226.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nConnecting the trailer is not very easy and the docking port doesn\u0027t allow much play while cornering but the solution is simple and sturdy. The trailer has it\u0027s own fuel cell and probe core so it can raise it\u0027s front wheels when the docking ports are in position.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWarning\u003C/strong\u003E: Kerbal Joint Reinforcement makes the suspension rigid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nDownload link: \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Azimech/77I--LRHF\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Azimech/77I--LRHF\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EUral 4320\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/uHYvA/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nSturdy soviet truck.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nFeatures:\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nComplex suspension to survive rough terrain and heavy loads.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nEight wheels on the rear axles.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nDouble fuel cell array.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n200 Units of fuel.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nStock, works fine without KerbPaint.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EWarning\u003C/strong\u003E: Kerbal Joint Reinforcement makes the suspension rigid.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nAction group 1: start fuel cell array.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nDownload link:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Azimech/Ural-4320\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Azimech/Ural-4320\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E1960\u0027s Pickup Truck\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/CL2j1/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nUpdated version from 1.0.4. Reduced part count from 191 to 166, redone styling front \u0026amp; rear, lowered mass with 3 tons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nAction group 1: start fuel cell array.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nDownload link:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalx.com/Azimech/77I--1960s-Pickup-version-2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbalx.com/Azimech/77I--1960s-Pickup-version-2\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETTZ Long Distance Truck\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\nI never expanded on the TTZ because I suddenly got interested in doing the Elcano challenge, august 2015. Notable evolution in building style.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe class=\u0022imgur-album\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022550\u0022 src=\u0022//imgur.com/a/kFkbS/embed?background=ffffff\u0026amp;text=1a1a1a\u0026amp;link=4e76c9\u0022 width=\u0022100%\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFeatures advanced suspension, this baby weighs 38 tons when the tank is full. Probably able to drive to the north pole. Keep cornering speeds below 20 m/s and you\u0027re safe.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAction group 1: start fuel cell array.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDownload link: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalx.com/crafts/4643\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://kerbalx.com/crafts/4643\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-26T13:30:54Z\u0022 title=\u002202/26/2016 01:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Azimech\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ENew truck added.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-25T09:43:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRewrote the OP and added the LRHF.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T01:36:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI didn\u0027t want to pollute the topic but I have this comment to make on vehicle sturdiness, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/61954-majorjim/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002261954\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/61954-majorjim/\u0022\u003E@Majorjim\u003C/a\u003E. Have you ever seen video\u0027s on semi-truck jumping? It shows these things can indeed survive a whole lot of punishment, because of the simple rule they have to transform/convert a huge amount of force \u0026amp; torque in real life. And my point with the breaking of wheels with a bump is this: it directly translates with hauling capacity. Increase the load on a construction which has no ability to dampen and divert forces over a greater area and the wheels will take the brunt of it. In real life kinetic energy is being converted into ... for example heat. A pulse can have disastrous effects but if the pulse is being dissipated into a gradual wave you get less load on all the load bearing structures overall. I can\u0027t use formulas because I never learned them ... just visualize what\u0027s happening.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, I invite you and others to take the truck for a spin :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jon144","CreatedById":80626,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T02:09:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat you did with the headlights is really creative! I haven\u0027t seen that before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T02:10:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222430093\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119143\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456452597\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280626\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jon144\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Jon144 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat you did with the headlights is really creative! I haven\u0027t seen that before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Azimech","CreatedById":50750,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-26T02:14:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222430093\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022119143\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221456452597\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280626\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jon144\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, Jon144 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat you did with the headlights is really creative! I haven\u0027t seen that before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI copied the idea from this post:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/39663-open-source-construction-techniques-for-craft-aesthetics/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=2278238\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, thank you \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index